<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum75/HTML/000157.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#400000"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#400000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Mallissin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Simply said, remove the damn dots.<P>It was bad enough that newbies that got coords off a cheat site, were hunting my territory I took 3 deaths to find, but now, why bother going to even the cheat sites with the Points of Interest.<P>Long are the days past of selling the location of a nice hunting spot, earned by a hardy explorer who took the time to explore the wilds. The day of the newbie has arrived!<P>Or has it?<P>(Remove the frickin things! <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif">)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Gelum Fyre</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">I'm hoping they are doing this for Beta only - so we are encouraged to "test out" relatively unvisited areas.  I agree, they should not be there.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Joe Napalm</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans"><BR>Oddly enough, most of the dots I've visited have been deserted. Of course, most of the dots I've visited are deep in the wilds surrounded my hordes of big, nasty critters...maybe that keeps the crowds away...grin.<P>I'm not saying I would be sad to see them go, though. It seems sort of silly that the map doesn't include the names of the towns, but shows the positions of dungeons in the Direlands.<P>-Jn-</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Ping Lo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">I don't really see a problem with them.  Weigh them out...<P>Pros:<BR>  Gives people a reason to leave the towns.  The less people in the towns, the better.<BR>  Many newbies will be afraid to just "head out into nowhere."  Now they at least have somewhere to go.  They can say to their friends "Hey, lets go try to get to that dot to the east."<P>Cons:<BR>  Destinations might become crowded now that they are obvious to everyone.  This makes the assumption that your average player can survive at point of interest and that the treasure/xp is worth staying for.<BR>  Instead of discovering places by scouring the countryside, more people will be inclined only to hop between points of interest.<P>Doesn't seem so bad to me when viewed that way.  You know they are't going to put the *best* places on the map.  It would be a waste.  People need to be rewarded for their discoveries, not rewarded for simply surviving the run.  I don't think all you powergamers have a lot to worry about.  But everyone else and the newbies that are sick of crowded towns have much to gain.<p>[This message has been edited by Ping Lo (edited October 13, 1999).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Ethos</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">E-Mail acss@stratics.com regarding this if you feel one way or another about it... because we don't presently have any forum moderators reporting data and I'll probably forget to check back unless this thread gets a lot of attention. <P>You've seen the way we've handled points of interest at ACSS now that the data is back up in the statistics section - so my question is this: How do you think we should handle the influx of interest points we get every week? My thoughts are to do a little rumor-style blurb on each one and a rough description of where to look if you want to venture out and try to find it. This avoids giving an exact location but still allows us to list enough spots that you'll always have a new adventure when you log on.<P>------------------<BR>Ian Armstrong (Ethos)<BR>Network Development<BR>StraticsCom, Inc.<BR>http://www.stratics.com<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">M. seandhi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">i have to agree, remove the dots and don't post coord's, this will give a benefit to clans and buying information from the innkeeps<P>------------------<BR>Peace and knowledge, attained through war and censorship; every rulers goal.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Jet</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">umm, lads have you been out to any of these PoI's?  I generally solo, unless I am doing something with my guild or just a couple of vassles, I have been to mabey a dozen of these PoI', three or four of them were unatanable, at one of them there were mages at the shadow ruin chessing shadows through walls, other than that I have yet to encounter anyone at them.  I have recently been cleaning out every hole in the desert (I am searching for the Silifi of Crimson Stars, while I dont think it is really there yet at least it is something to do) I started with rumors from inkeeps for more or less newbie holes, and end up stagering across holes all the time, I have checked the cheat lists of dungeons, and submited to them over the course of my travels. Heh, I have even taken parchment, wrote down teasers and given them out to 1/2 dozen random people at a time.. and why not?  This world is perfectly big enuff to find room to fight.. Now if you Lads are talking about "good" hunting spots being somewhere you can chesse your enemy to death with spells or shafts I dont feel remotely bad about ruining your day heh<P>Xao Jet<BR>19th lvl Warrior/Theif/Merchant<BR>Leafcull<BR> <A HREF="http://www.martilaistsguild.com" TARGET=_blank>www.martilaistsguild.com</A> <BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
